# Aleppo

A web-first recipe management app — a "cooking diary" in the spirit of Strava/Letterboxd. Users save recipes, log every cook with a date and note, and follow friends to see what they've been cooking. Full spec: `docs/PRD.md`.

## Stack

| Layer | Choice |
|-------|--------|
| Framework | Next.js 15 (App Router) |
| Language | TypeScript (strict) |
| ORM | Drizzle ORM + Drizzle Kit migrations |
| Auth | Auth.js v5 — credentials (email/pw); Google OAuth code present but UI removed pending credentials |
| Database | PostgreSQL 16 — Railway managed add-on |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui |
| Images | Cloudflare R2 via `@aws-sdk/client-s3`; `sharp` for server-side resize |
| URL scraping | `@extractus/recipe-extractor` (Schema.org JSON-LD first); Playwright fallback |
| AI (V2 only) | `@google/generative-ai` — Gemini 2.5 Flash |
| Hosting | Railway (Hobby plan) |

## Monetization

- Core product is **free, no limits** (recipes, logging, social, import)
- **Free tier**: 10 AI imports per month — covers casual users
- **Lifetime (~$15 one-time)**: 500 AI imports per month — for heavy users and cookbook digitizers; cap deters abuse, not revenue extraction
- No subscriptions; Stripe used only for a single one-time product (not needed until V2 AI ships)
- AI costs (Gemini Flash ~$0.001/import) are low enough to absorb at early scale; the lifetime fee covers costs for power users

## Key Conventions

- **Never auto-save imports** — always show a review/edit step before persisting
- **Recipe privacy defaults to private** — `recipes.is_public` defaults to `false`; user profiles default to public (`users.is_public` defaults to `true`). Both must be true for content to appear in follower feeds
- **Ingredients dual storage** — store both `raw` (original string) and parsed `{amount, unit, name, notes}` fields; never discard the original
- **Recipe import audit trail** — every import writes a `recipe_imports` row with `raw_payload` (jsonb) for debugging
- **Images always re-uploaded to R2** — never store third-party image URLs long-term; download and re-host on import
- **No Redis, no job queues, no tRPC at MVP** — keep the stack simple until there's a reason to add complexity
- **Attribution tracking** — `recipes.isAdapted` (bool) is set when recipe content fields change via edit; `recipes.commentsUrl` stores a link to the original page's comments section, auto-detected on import (DOM scan + `config/comment-anchors.json` site map for JS-heavy sites)
- **Import URL is the primary add-recipe action** — the nav and mobile bottom tab both lead with "Import URL"; "New recipe" (manual) is secondary

## Implementation Status

**V1.0 MVP is complete and in active use.** Post-MVP polish and attribution features have been shipped on top.

